Not sure if this applies,  it just popped into my head.  Since this is a brain storming session, I wanted to chime in.

Would there be a case for @Rule to be added to Parameterized instances.  The reason I asked this, back in the day when I could contribute, I suggested/submitted a patch for @BeforeParameterized @AfterParameterized. (Issue 45)  My mind just associated the two after seeing the discussion of Rules for Suites.

This makes me think that each unit test and grouping of unit test needs some things... setup, tear down, assertions, and invariants.  It may be the case that all groupings of units needs to have these things.  Thus if you group at the Suite, Parameter, Class all things need to be present.

Am I making sense?

Big Mike

